\par }\pard \widctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 As anyone with Quake editing experience will know, the use of prefabs is a very important for speed of building levels and for giving a consistent feel to level or group of levels.  Of course you don\rquote 
t want to over do it, but use as needed and most importantly submit prefab areas for upload.  Please place your prefabs at 0,0,0 for ease of importation.  If you have made something that you can\rquote t use in your area, but you think it\rquote 
s cool, prefab and upload it anyway.  There is no reason for any good work to go to waste.  Even if it is not directly used it may be able to be modified or may be an inspiration for something else.
\par 
\par All prefabs for this pak }{\b\fs24 MUST}{\fs24  be original.  It is OK to get ideas from other levels/prefabs, but anything we make must not be a direct copy of someone else\rquote s work.  Again, be original.
\par 
\par Since Quake2 is a unit based game, there is an opportunity to have areas do double duty.  You may want to mak
e some of your areas visible to different levels, but not yet accessible.  If you are working on a unit with another person, you will want to prefab this area and upload 
